In this part of the OSVR Quick Start, we will go over what software you need to download and install to get OSVR to work with Unreal Engine 4 (UE4).

1. Click on the following link to bring up the OSVR Developer Portal web page. 

	**[https://osvr.github.io/using/](https://osvr.github.io/using/)**

1. On the OSVR Developer page, locate the **OSVR Runtime for Windows**  option and then click on the **Download** option to download the OSVR Windows drivers.

	[REGION:lightbox]
	[![](OSVR_Driver_Download.png)(w:640 h:336)](OSVR_Driver_Download.png)
	[/REGION]
	
	[REGION:caption]
	Click for full image.
	[/REGION]

1. After the OSVR Runtime for Windows has finished downloading, locate the installer and begin the install process. 

1. Once the install is completed locate the OSVR folder and look for the **osvr_server.exe** and double - click on it to run it.

	[REGION:lightbox]
	[![](OSVR_Server_Location.png)(w:407 h:293)](OSVR_Server_Location.png)
	[/REGION]
	
	[REGION:caption]
	Click for full image.
	[/REGION]

1. When the OSVR server launches you will the following command line window being displayed.

	![](OSVR_Server_Windows.png)

	[region:note]
	For UE4 to use OSVR you will need to launch the OSVR sever **Before** you launch your UE4 project.
	[/region]

In the next section of the OSVR Quick Start, we will go over how to create a UE4 project to work with OSVR.

